President Muhammadu Buhari on Thursday met behind closed doors with former President, Goodluck Jonathan, at the Presidential Villa, Abuja, according to the News Agency of Nigeria. The former president arrived the State House at about 3:00pm and went straight to the President’s office. The agenda of the meeting between the two men was unknown as of the time of this report. Jonathan, who is visiting the Presidential Villa for the fifth time since leaving power, was last seen in Aso Rock in 2016.